text.section:
Real property is a class of property and is divided into the following subclasses:
land that is actively devoted to farm or agricultural use, assessed under § 8-209 of this title;
marshland, assessed under § 8-210 of this title;
woodland, assessed under § 8-211 of this title;
land of a country club or golf course, assessed under §§ 8-212 through 8-217 of this title;
land that is used for a planned development, assessed under §§ 8-220 through 8-225 of this title;
rezoned real property that is used for residential purposes, assessed under §§ 8-226 through 8-228 of this title;
operating real property of a railroad;
operating real property of a public utility;
property valued under § 8-105(a)(3) of this subtitle;
conservation property, assessed under § 8-209.1 of this title; and
all other real property that is directed by this article to be assessed.

Personal property is a class of property and is divided into the following subclasses:
stock in business;
distilled spirits;
operating personal property of a railroad;
operating personal property of a public utility that is machinery or equipment used to generate electricity or steam for sale;
all other operating personal property of a public utility;
machinery and equipment, other than operating personal property of a public utility, that is used to generate:
electricity or steam for sale; or
hot or chilled water for sale that is used to heat or cool a building; and
all other personal property that is directed by this article to be assessed.
